ANDRES ESCOBAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In response to "Gunmen Kill Soccer Player in Colombia," July 3: 
</P>
<P>
 Goodby soccer. Adios World Cup. The ambush that killed a World Cup soccer 
player in Medellin, Colombia may have also wounded an innocent bystander in 
America: 
</P>
<P>
 Popular interest. 
</P>
<P>
 Next year, after all the hoopla has subsided here in this country, interest in 
a sport that uses only half the human body will probably have died like the 
unfortunate Andres Escobar -- leaving a blip on the screen of the average 
living room television no bigger than a bloodstain. 
</P>
<P>
 DOUGLAS HERMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Monica 
</P>
<P>
 * Regarding the death of Andres Escobar because of his error in the first 
round of the World Cup soccer games: I believe Colombia should be banned from 
the World Cup the next time around. And if anything like that should happen 
again -- banned for life. 
</P>
<P>
 Those people are psychotic. 
</P>
<P>
 ERIN SCARLETT 
</P>
<P>
 Palm Desert 
