<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; OWN A PIECE OF THE ACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the "They'll do anything to make a dollar department," organizers of the 
New York/New Jersey World Cup venue are holding a public sod sale after 
Wednesday's semifinal at the Meadowlands. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bermuda Turfgrass field will be removed from Giants Stadium after the 
Italy-Bulgaria semifinal, so why not sell it? The sale begins at 6 a.m. 
Thursday.About 80,000 square feet of official World Cup turf will be available. 
</P>
<P>
 Alan Rothenberg, chairman of World Cup '94, said in a statement there is no 
better way of showing "our appreciation than to offer something special from 
the World Cup that the fans will cherish for a lifetime." 
</P>
<P>
 Because proceeds from the sale will be donated to the U.S. Soccer Federation 
Foundation, it will also benefit Rothenberg, USSF president. 
</P>
<P>
 The sod is going for $10 to $20 per square foot. Minimum orders of one square 
foot are $20. Call (201) 460-4144 or (201) 804-2871. ELLIOTT ALMOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
