<P>
 The Daily Telegraph consulted Brazilians in London to learn the background of 
various team names.Among the gems they came up with: Carlos Verri is Dunga, 
which translates as Dopey, because he was thought when young to resemble one of 
the Seven Dwarfs. Jorginho translates as Little George, Zinho as Tiny, Branco 
as Whitey, and Bebeto as Bobby. 
</P>
