<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; THE RIGHT TOUCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Perhaps Swedish forward-midfielder Henrik Larsson had the best approach when 
it came time for his turn during the high drama of Sunday's penalty kicks at 
Stanford Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't think so much," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Larsson was the final Swedish player to kick against Romanian goalkeeper 
Florin Prunea. His kick gave Sweden a 5-4 advantage and the victory when 
Romania's Midorag Belodedici couldn't score on his attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 "I decided which corner I should put it in, then I looked at the goalkeeper," 
Larsson said. "He was going the other way, and then I put it in the goal. I 
would kick it hard if he was going in the same direction, loosely if he was 
going the other." LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
