<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94: SEMIFINALS; SPOTLIGHT; IT'S NO EMERGENCY UNTIL THE GAME'S 
OVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousands of jubilant Swedish soccer fans jammed the streets early Monday, 
celebrating the victory over Romania in the World Cup quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Stockholm Police had to intervene to help a pregnant woman with labor pains 
get through the milling crowd and traffic. 
</P>
<P>
 The emergency service operator in Malmo said no phone calls were made during 
the game. But after goalkeeper Thomas Ravelli had saved his second penalty 
kick, ensuring Sweden a place in the semifinals, a woman called to say her 
husband had chest pains and needed assistance. 
</P>
<P>
 "I wanted to call earlier but he forbade me," the woman told the emergency 
operator, according to the national news agency TT. 
</P>
