<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAIDERS; LINEMAN POWERS RE-SIGNS; COLLINS CUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The door to the Raider training camp in Oxnard is swinging both ways. 
</P>
<P>
 Coming in Monday after signing were defensive lineman Warren Powers, a former 
Ram, and safety/special teams player Joe King. 
</P>
<P>
 Going out was receiver Shawn Collins, who failed his physical. 
</P>
<P>
 Powers is a five-year veteran out of Maryland who was drafted by the Denver 
Broncos and played for the Rams in 1992 and '93. He was signed by the Raiders 
before last season's playoffs, but never played. Powers was cut last month, 
then re-signed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 King, a three-year veteran out of Oklahoma State, has previously played for 
the Cincinnati Bengals, Cleveland Browns and Tampa Bay Buccaneers. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive lineman Jerry Ball, signed as a free agent last month, is expected 
to report to Oxnard tonight. He had been excused from the first few days of 
practice because of a prior commitment. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</TEXT>
