<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: BICYCLE LOCKERS TO BE INSTALLED AT METROLINK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoping to encourage Ventura County Metrolink commuters to ride bicycles 
instead of driving to the train station, a local agency is going to install 
storage lockers at stops throughout the county. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ventura County Transportation Commission has received an $80,000 federal 
Congestion Mitigation and Air Quality Improvement grant to buy the 
lockers.Caltrans has agreed to pay an additional $20,000 for administrative 
costs. 
</P>
<P>
 In the coming months, a total of at least 40 heavy-duty fiberglass lockers 
will be installed at the Metrolink stations in Simi Valley, Moorpark, Camarillo 
and Oxnard, as well as at the Thousand Oaks Civic Arts Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
 Users must supply their own locks and will have free access to lockers on a 
first-come, first-served basis. 
</P>
<P>
 Before selecting the lockers, commission staffers surveyed other cities with 
similar programs, including Santa Clarita, Riverside, Sacramento, Portland, 
Ore., and Spokane, Wash., to find the best equipment and program. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
