<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEIS CRITICIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The criticism of county Supt. of Schools Chuck Weis for displacing the 
political aspirations of Dan Flynn could be entirely unwarranted. Chuck 
undoubtedly intends to eliminate the other positions in the department and then 
resign to save money. 
</P>
<P>
 He probably has realized that in the interest of economy, the Ventura County 
School Board and his department -- another layer of unnecessary bureaucracy -- 
should be demolished as a wasteful anachronism of the horse and buggy days. 
