 Such an action could probably save $1 million a year for Ventura County 
education alone. And if the practice were extended to the other 58 counties, 
the savings could be more than $50 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Or maybe Chuck intends to replace Flynn with a newcomer at a much lower 
salary. With the savings, he could probably get the school board to give him a 
second raise this year. 
