GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; FIRE DEPARTMENT ADDS 19 RECRUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Burbank Fire Department has hired 19 probationary firefighters, its 
largest group of recruits ever, officials said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 All of the recruits must still complete a 10-week course before becoming 
full-fledged firefighters.If they pass, the new hires will replace the 
department's retiring firefighters and alleviate the overtime required of other 
firefighters, Battalion Chief Mario Gagnon said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The reason (the recruitment class) is so large is we had cutbacks a few years 
back," he said. "We lost six firefighters' positions, so we were able to get 
these positions back. 
</P>
<P>
 "The service will be the same, but there will be less wear and tear on our 
firefighters." 
</P>
<P>
 The department presently has 122 firefighters, Gagnon said. With some 
retirements expected soon, the department will be up to 133 after the recruits 
complete training. VIVIEN LOU CHEN 
</P>
