<TEXT>
<P>
 Ex-RV Dealer Pleads Guilty to Fraud: The former owner of now-bankrupt Sunset 
Motors, once the leading West Coast recreational vehicle dealership, pleaded 
guilty to bilking three community banks out of $2.8 million.William P. 
Whitledge Jr., whose $50-million network of RV sales stretched to Seattle, 
could face 30 years in prison and a $1-million fine for pledging the same RVs 
as collateral to get multiple loans from more than one bank. Whitledge also 
obtained liens against RVs he didn't own. Prosecutors said Whitledge was trying 
to prop up a company that was faltering from the recession. He is to be 
sentenced Oct. 17. 
</P>
