</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Digital, General Instrument in Interactive Deal: Digital Equipment Corp. of 
Maynard, Mass., and General Instrument Corp. of Chicago said they will work 
together in the emerging market of systems offering access to an array of 
information, such as movies and home shopping services, over television sets. 
DEC, the nation's third-largest maker of computers, will supply servers and 
software, and General Instrument is to supply the access boxes. The 
non-exclusive agreement is significant to DEC because General Instrument 
controls about 65% of the market for the boxes. 
</P>
