<P>
BRIEFLY: COMPANY TOWN ANNEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CBS Vote Expected on QVC: The CBS Inc. board was expected to endorse Chairman 
Laurence A. Tisch's plan to merge the broadcasting company with QVC Inc., the 
cable shopping concern headed by Barry Diller, by the end of the week. 
Speculation persisted on Wall Street that a third party could emerge as a 
spoiler of the proposed transaction, but many industry analysts consider that 
unlikely."Chances are getting slimmer as the days go by," said Ed Atorino, 
media analyst at Dillon Read & Co. Walt Disney Co. is often mentioned as being 
interested in buying some, if not all, of CBS. The filmmaker and theme park 
operator is a major supplier of TV programs, and involvement with a network 
would assure it of distribution. However, Disney watchers say the company is 
unlikely to intervene. 
