<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CREATIVE COMPUTER'S INCOME RISES IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Creative Computer Applications Inc., a Calabasas-based company that sells 
automated data-handling systems for hospitals and medical laboratories, 
reported a sharp rise in net income for its fiscal third quarter that ended May 
31. 
</P>
<P>
 Net income for the quarter was $286,313, compared to $90,013 in net income 
reported for the same quarter a year ago.Sales for the quarter were up slightly 
to $1.85 million from $1.82 million a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine-month period that ended May 31, the company reported a net loss 
of $88,892 on sales of $3.95 million. A year earlier, the company reported net 
income of $121,163 on sales of $4.66 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said the nine-month results were hampered by damage to facilities 
caused by the Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake. Steven M. Besbeck, chief executive 
of the company, said the quake triggered the office sprinkler system, soaking 
equipment and inventory, and disrupting operations for seven weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
