</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dole Food Co., a Westlake Village producer of fruit, vegetables, juice and 
nuts, said its second-quarter profit was $35.7 million, up 10% from $32.4 
million in net income in the same period the previous year.Revenue for the 
quarter, which ended June 18, was $987 million, up 14% from $864 million the 
previous year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months that ended June 18, Dole reported a profit of $65.4 
million, up 6% from a $61.9-million profit in the same period a year earlier. 
Revenue for the six months was $1.81 billion, up 11% from $1.63 billion in 
1993. 
