<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; CLASS PARTICIPANTS TO GET MACE CERTIFICATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rancho Santiago College District will offer a class on the proper use of 
Mace on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The course will cover the legal rights and responsibilities regarding all 
forms of self-defense, how to avoid being a crime victim and what to do when 
victimized in a violent crime, district spokesman Dale Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The cost of the course is $30. On completion, participants will receive a 
lifetime certification from the state Department of Justice to carry and 
purchase Mace. Students 16 to 18 years old may enroll but must have a parental 
consent form to do so, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar will be from 7 to 9 p.m. in Room R-113 at the Rancho Santiago 
campus, at 17th and Bristol streets. 
