car with rival gang members passed near the intersection of Pomona and Townsend 
streets late Sunday afternoon, Arenas ran out of his house with the shotgun and 
fired once, Helton said. A stray pellet pierced the boy's back as he played in 
his driveway nearby. 
</P>
<P>
 Hernandez, who was at Arenas' house at the time, is being held as an 
accomplice, Helton said. Both man were being held on $250,000 bail. Helton said 
the weapon was not found. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have released one other suspect held for questioning. 
